<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1871-03-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1871-03-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="54" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d54">
                            <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-chapter-head">[Protocol of
                                Conference between the High Commissioners on the Part of the United
                                States of America and the High Commissioners of Great
                                Britain]</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1871-03-14"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 14,
                                        1871</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The High Commissioners having met, the protocol of the conference
                                held on the 13th of March was read and confirmed.</p>
                            <p>The High Commissioners then proceeded with the consideration ot the
                                matters referred to them.</p>
                            <p>The conference was adjourned to the 15th of March.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <list>
                                        <item>J. C. BANCROFT DAVIS.</item>
                                        <item>TENTERDEN.</item>
                                    </list>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>